Lagos – Nigerian pirates have been fingered in the hijack of a fishing vessel, MARINE 711 with 40 crew on-board including  five Koreans, Greek, kidnapped in Gulf of Guinea while en route to anchovies fishing grounds. The incident happened on March 26, 2018, in Volta region waters, Ghana, Gulf of Guinea. The pirates, however, left vessel on March 28, taking with them, at least five hostages, including the Captain, Chief Officer and Chief Engineer of Korean nationality; alongside other two, who are Ghanaian and Greek. The released vessel reportedly drifted for some time before being taken by Ghana Navy to Tema Port. Meanwhile, a fast ferry, ELDORADO with 403 passengers on board collided with unidentified object in Japan sea in the evening March 31, while en route from Dokdo to Ulleundo island, Korea, while moving at some 28 knots speed. The hull was breached, with ensuing water ingress in the engine room area. The water ingress was put under control by crew using pumps, and ferry managed to reach Ulleungdo at reduced speed but under own power, escorted by Korean Patrol ship. No injury was reported. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.